## Convolution

$$
K, K' \isin \R^{M \times N} \quad K(m, n) = K'(M-1-m, N-1-n)
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
( I * K )_{ij}
&= \sum_m \sum_n {I(i+m, j+n)K(M-1-m, N-1-n)} \\
&= \sum_m \sum_n {I(i+m, j+n)K'(m, n)} &= (I \otimes K')_{ij}
\end{aligned}
$$

